b'We have to have the will to put our country on a sustainable fiscal path. #BIToomey'
b'A strong economic recovery is possible. It\xe2\x80\x99s up to us. #BIToomey'
b"Pro-growth tax reform would kickstart a surge of investment and economic growth. We would see the recovery we've been waiting for. #BIToomey"
b"If we put entitlements on sustainable path, we ensure their survival. Most important thing to avoid fiscal crisis we're courting. #BIToomey"
b'We need to reform the entitlement programs driving our fiscal problems -- we have to agree on the fundamental problem. #BIToomey'
b"There's little dispute if we do pro-growth tax reform right, it will generate economic growth and the jobs that come with it. #BIToomey"
b'We can use the next year to do what we need \xe2\x80\x93 pro-growth tax reform. #BIToomey'
b"We should extend the current tax rates for another year; they've been in place for 12 yrs. Then use next year to reform tax code. #BIToomey"
b'I think there\xe2\x80\x99s a better way than going over the fiscal cliff, as some of my colleagues have recommended. #BIToomey'
b'Our plan ensured the lower brackets did not have increases. The tax code would become more progressive, not less progressive. #BIToomey'
b"That's why I find it so objectionable that those who knew better say we wanted to increase taxes on middle class to pay for rich. #BIToomey"
b'We stipulated right at the beginning of this arrangement that all net new revenue come from the top two brackets. #BIToomey'
b'Strong bipartisan consensus that we needed corp. tax reform. Supercommittee had unlimited jurisdiction -- we could have done that. #BIToomey'
b'My supercommittee proposal offered $500B of new revenue. We were meeting them at the halfway point. #BIToomey'
b'Any new revenue had to come in conjunction with new pro-growth tax reform, which bipartisan deficit commissions have recommended. #BIToomey'
b'Democrats wanted a huge tax increase, but they were not willing to begin to solve the real problem. #BIToomey'
b'What Republican supercommittee members wanted was to make structural reforms to at least one entitlement, make it sustainable. #BIToomey'
b'No significant government program can grow faster than our economy indefinitely. All three big entitlements are growing faster. #BIToomey'
